===Pronunciation===

:lime' stone
===Noun===

#An abundant [[rock]] of [[marine]] and fresh-water [[sediment]]s. Primarily composed of [[calcite]]. Limestone occurs in a variety of forms, both [[crystal]]line and [[amorphous]]. 

=== Chemical composition ===
*Calcium carbonate, <math>CaCO_3</math>
 
=== Physical properties ===

*Color: White, gray, pink, yellowish, brown to black 
*Luster: Usually earthy. Crystal planes may be reflective
*Fracture: Uneven

